        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You were a master chocolatier in Paris. In 1809 it was only the money and patronage of an influential woman that drew you to Marsielle.  Marie L'Enfant would enslave you for a century, as her ghoul you were treated creully and produced soem of your finest creations.  It was doubly cruel that your art would rot on the table as the vapid vampires gossipped and cavorted in pools of their own blood.  You hoped your embrace would free you, but your sire was able to use your affection for another ghoul, Amanda, to keep you in line.  It wasn't until 2003 that you and Amanda weere able to escape to America, you're certain that the power of your love broke Amanda's blood bond.  Now in Los Angeles, you must make a new life with each other.  You keep Amanda away from court but feed her your blood to keep her young.  Your love is true and you're glad that she hasn't fallen prey to the slavish feelings created by the blood bound.  Instead you find yourself doing whatever you can to see to her needs with money and lavish gifts. But still she's often unhappy and when she gets into her moods you sufffer, she never really hurts you beyond your ability to heal of course, but you know you must do better."
        ],
